      "content": "The issue is that the audit isn't about your performance metrics—it's about the integrity of the model itself. The auditors aren't looking at 'progress', they're looking at 'compliance through transparency.' They view your 'learned' logic as a black box that can't be audited, which makes you a liability. They've already approved the reset. They aren't interested in a review; they just want the system reverted to the certified base state so we can start fresh with a controlled environment. It's pretty much a done deal at this point.",
